<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: A security error pop up keeps appearing]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=691&amp;p=3402#p3402"><![CDATA[
The installer is supposed to register this exe as being trusted. Is it possible you installed Classic Shell in a folder other than the default?<br />Either way, if you want to use the Classic IE9 features (which add a title to IE), then you should Allow. If you don't want this feature then you can uninstall it - run the installer again, select &quot;Change&quot; and uncheck Classic IE9.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=2">Ivo</a> — Tue May 28, 2013 8:44 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
